init_text:
Once upon a time there was an old mother pig who had one hundred little pigs and not enough food to feed them. So when they were old enough, she sent them out into the world to seek their fortunes. You know the story about the first three little pigs. This is a story about the 92nd little pig.

The 92nd little pig built a house out of depleted uranium. And the wolf was like, "dude."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The wolf was like, "dude, I'm going to blow your house down."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: So the wolf huffed and puffed and blew and blew, but the house withstood the wolf's mighty huffing and puffing

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: So the wolf huffed and puffed and huffed and puffed and huffed and puffed.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: But the wolf's huffing and puffing was not enough to blow down the house.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He was very angry that he could not blow down that house.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The wolf was very angry, but he was also very hungry.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The wolf knew that Dr. Oliver's mother had a hundred little pigs.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The wolf knew that Dr. Oliver was the 92nd little pig.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Dr. Oliver was not surprised that the wolf knew this.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The wolf asked Dr. Oliver if he could have one of his siblings for dinner.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Dr. Oliver was not going to let that happen.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He was going to do whatever it took to protect his siblings from the wolf.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: So he told the wolf that he would give him one of his siblings for dinner, but only if the wolf promised to leave the rest of his siblings

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: So Dr. Oliver led the wolf to the home of his brother, Dr. Cornelius Oliver, Jr. The wolf was very surprised

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The wolf had expected the little pig to be more difficult.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Smith had built his house out of lead.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: So the wolf huffed and puffed and huffed and puffed, but Smith's house stayed fully intact.
